results.name: Number of strictly inferior prime-power divisors of n.
comment: We define a divisor d|n to be strictly inferior if d < n/d. Strictly inferior divisors are counted by A056924 and listed by A341674.
example: The strictly inferior prime-power divisors of n!:
xref: The weakly inferior version is A333750.
The version for odd instead of prime-power divisors is A333805.
The version for prime instead of prime-power divisors is A333806.
The weakly superior version is A341593.
The version for squarefree instead of prime-power divisors is A341596.
The strictly superior version is A341644.
A001221 counts prime divisors, with sum A001414.
A056924 counts strictly superior (or strictly inferior) divisors.
